{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-post-template-post-template-tsx","path":"/blog/software-development-and-programming-tools-in-2022","result":{"data":{"markdownRemark":{"id":"322eff88-01b5-5ff2-b8a1-1ae798ad7565","html":"<p>Welcome back! ðŸ”¥\nI havenâ€™t written anything in a long time, as Iâ€™ve been very busy for the past six months. However, after this time I am back and hopefully permanently.</p>\n<p>My programming skills have developed a lot since the last time I wrote on my blog. I owe this to my curiosity for technology and advanced programming tools.</p>\n<p>In this article, I will provide you with an updated list of applications that I use on a daily basis in my work.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: I have already written <a href=\"https://pietrzakadrian.com/blog/my-software-development-setup-and-programming-tools-october-2021\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">one such article in October 2021</a>. You can check how much this list has changed.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<hr>\n<h1 id=\"ide\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#ide\" aria-label=\"ide permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>IDE</h1>\n<p>I have been using Visual Studio Code for many years. Here I wanted to show you my settings.json file, however, since I started using <a href=\"https://www.jetbrains.com/idea/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><strong>IntelliJ IDEA</strong></a>, the quality of my projects has gone to a much higher level. ðŸ“ˆ</p>\n<p>The code editor is ready to use right out of the box. It is not a free license, but it is definitely worth investing in.</p>\n<h2 id=\"theme\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#theme\" aria-label=\"theme permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Theme</h2>\n<p>I was looking for a good theme. I had been in love with <a href=\"https://marketplace.visualstudio.com/items?itemName=teabyii.ayu\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Ayu Mirage</a> for many years, but this year that changed.</p>\n<p>For me, it was important that there was not too strong a contrast between the source code and the background. I think I have found my true love.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://plugins.jetbrains.com/plugin/10321-nord\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><strong>Nord</strong></a> is the best theme I have ever used. The oceanic look is very calming and allows for maximum focus. ðŸŒŠ</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: Nord theme is also used in code listings on my blog.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<h2 id=\"plugins\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#plugins\" aria-label=\"plugins permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Plugins</h2>\n<p>As I wrote above, IntelliJ is ready to work efficiently right out of the box. However, the available plug-ins can significantly speed up writing source code and improve quality.</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.tabnine.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><strong>Tabnine: Code Faster with AI Code Completions</strong></a> is an alternative to Copilot (free, local option, privacy). It suggests what you want to write and is extremely accurate at it. I canâ€™t imagine programming today without this tool. The value of Tabnine in terms of productivity. Tabnine for <a href=\"https://www.tabnine.com/enterprise\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">enterprises</a>;</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://plugins.jetbrains.com/plugin/10456-prettier\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><strong>Prettier</strong></a> is a very good tool for formatting code;</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://plugins.jetbrains.com/plugin/9792-key-promoter-x\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><strong>Key Promoter X</strong></a> is a plugin for displaying keyboard shortcut prompts to perform given actions faster;</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://plugins.jetbrains.com/plugin/7495--ignore\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><strong>.ignore</strong></a> is a plugin that supports ignoring files added to the repository (via .gitignore file).</li>\n</ol>\n<p>Thatâ€™s all that can be useful. All other tools are built into the IDE.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 960px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ed29e30243aa60eb952f75d6257ae630/a2b91/ide.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.5%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/ed29e30243aa60eb952f75d6257ae630/8ac56/ide.webp 240w,\n/static/ed29e30243aa60eb952f75d6257ae630/d3be9/ide.webp 480w,\n/static/ed29e30243aa60eb952f75d6257ae630/e46b2/ide.webp 960w,\n/static/ed29e30243aa60eb952f75d6257ae630/f992d/ide.webp 1440w,\n/static/ed29e30243aa60eb952f75d6257ae630/882b9/ide.webp 1920w,\n/static/ed29e30243aa60eb952f75d6257ae630/1ab77/ide.webp 3360w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/ed29e30243aa60eb952f75d6257ae630/8ff5a/ide.png 240w,\n/static/ed29e30243aa60eb952f75d6257ae630/e85cb/ide.png 480w,\n/static/ed29e30243aa60eb952f75d6257ae630/d9199/ide.png 960w,\n/static/ed29e30243aa60eb952f75d6257ae630/07a9c/ide.png 1440w,\n/static/ed29e30243aa60eb952f75d6257ae630/29114/ide.png 1920w,\n/static/ed29e30243aa60eb952f75d6257ae630/a2b91/ide.png 3360w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/ed29e30243aa60eb952f75d6257ae630/d9199/ide.png\"\n            alt=\"IDE\"\n            title=\"IDE\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<hr>\n<h1 id=\"terminal\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#terminal\" aria-label=\"terminal permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Terminal</h1>\n<p>Terminal is the second most important tool for working as a software developer. If you are looking for something modern, <a href=\"https://www.warp.dev/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">Warp</a> will be a good option for you.</p>\n<p>I prefer the standard solutions that <a href=\"https://iterm2.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><strong>iTerm2</strong></a> offers - it works very well.</p>\n<p>In addition, I use the <strong>zsh</strong> shell with <strong>zsh-autosuggestions</strong>, <strong>zsh-syntax-highlighting</strong>, <strong>Web Search</strong> plugins and <a href=\"https://ohmyz.sh/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><strong>Oh My Zsh</strong></a> framework. I recommend using the <a href=\"https://github.com/hwyncho/ayu-iTerm\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><strong>Ayu Mirage theme iTerm</strong></a>.</p>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 960px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/de14caced9e9750336248c9c4e42a4df/010dc/terminal.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 52.916666666666664%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <picture>\n          <source\n              srcset=\"/static/de14caced9e9750336248c9c4e42a4df/8ac56/terminal.webp 240w,\n/static/de14caced9e9750336248c9c4e42a4df/d3be9/terminal.webp 480w,\n/static/de14caced9e9750336248c9c4e42a4df/e46b2/terminal.webp 960w,\n/static/de14caced9e9750336248c9c4e42a4df/f992d/terminal.webp 1440w,\n/static/de14caced9e9750336248c9c4e42a4df/91564/terminal.webp 1714w\"\n              sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n              type=\"image/webp\"\n            />\n          <source\n            srcset=\"/static/de14caced9e9750336248c9c4e42a4df/8ff5a/terminal.png 240w,\n/static/de14caced9e9750336248c9c4e42a4df/e85cb/terminal.png 480w,\n/static/de14caced9e9750336248c9c4e42a4df/d9199/terminal.png 960w,\n/static/de14caced9e9750336248c9c4e42a4df/07a9c/terminal.png 1440w,\n/static/de14caced9e9750336248c9c4e42a4df/010dc/terminal.png 1714w\"\n            sizes=\"(max-width: 960px) 100vw, 960px\"\n            type=\"image/png\"\n          />\n          <img\n            class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n            src=\"/static/de14caced9e9750336248c9c4e42a4df/d9199/terminal.png\"\n            alt=\"IDE\"\n            title=\"IDE\"\n            loading=\"lazy\"\n            decoding=\"async\"\n            style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n          />\n        </picture>\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<hr>\n<h1 id=\"focus\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#focus\" aria-label=\"focus permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Focus</h1>\n<p>One of my biggest discoveries that has increased my productivity by 300% is getting into the right state of focus. It may sound surprising, but thatâ€™s what itâ€™s all about.</p>\n<p><a href=\"https://code.endel.io/?code=adrianpietrzak\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><strong>Endel</strong></a> is a sound wellness app helping you focus, relax, and sleep and backed by neuroscience. Available on multiple platforms, it creates soundscapes that adapt to your heart rate, motion, time of the day, weather, and circadian rhythm. ðŸŽ¶</p>\n<p>I use this app every day for several hours at a time. I am doing it even now, while writing this article.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><strong>Note</strong>: you can try Endel for free by clicking on this <a href=\"https://code.endel.io/?code=adrianpietrzak\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\">link</a>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<hr>\n<h1 id=\"other-tools\" style=\"position:relative;\"><a href=\"#other-tools\" aria-label=\"other tools permalink\" class=\"anchor before\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" focusable=\"false\" height=\"16\" version=\"1.1\" viewBox=\"0 0 16 16\" width=\"16\"><path fill-rule=\"evenodd\" d=\"M4 9h1v1H4c-1.5 0-3-1.69-3-3.5S2.55 3 4 3h4c1.45 0 3 1.69 3 3.5 0 1.41-.91 2.72-2 3.25V8.59c.58-.45 1-1.27 1-2.09C10 5.22 8.98 4 8 4H4c-.98 0-2 1.22-2 2.5S3 9 4 9zm9-3h-1v1h1c1 0 2 1.22 2 2.5S13.98 12 13 12H9c-.98 0-2-1.22-2-2.5 0-.83.42-1.64 1-2.09V6.25c-1.09.53-2 1.84-2 3.25C6 11.31 7.55 13 9 13h4c1.45 0 3-1.69 3-3.5S14.5 6 13 6z\"></path></svg></a>Other tools</h1>\n<p>Depending on the type of software development, these tools change. However, I use several programs every time:</p>\n<ol>\n<li><a href=\"https://brave.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><strong>Brave</strong></a> - top one web browser based on Chromium engine;</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://rectangleapp.com/pro\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><strong>Rectangle Pro</strong></a> - quicker window snapping on macOS;</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.tunabellysoftware.com/tgpro/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><strong>TG Pro</strong></a> for controlling my MacBookâ€™s temperature;</li>\n<li>I clean the temporary files once a month using the <a href=\"https://macpaw.audw.net/c/3627891/66209/1733\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><strong>CleanMyMac X</strong></a>;</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://www.postman.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><strong>Postman</strong></a> - REST API client;</li>\n<li><a href=\"https://binarynights.com/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"nofollow noopener noreferrer\"><strong>ForkLift 3</strong></a> - FTP client.</li>\n</ol>\n<p>My experience has shown that you donâ€™t need many programs to produce software efficiently. Fewer programs keep your computer cleaner. This also helps to better manage the work.</p>\n<hr>\n<p>In this article you learned about my list of applications for software development. I guarantee you that the programs listed are the best tools available at this time.</p>","timeToRead":4,"fields":{"slug":"/posts/2022-09-14---Software-Development-and-Programming-Tools-In-2022//blog/software-development-and-programming-tools-in-2022","tagSlugs":["/blog/tag/computer-setup/","/blog/tag/programming-tools/"]},"frontmatter":{"date":"2022-09-14T22:40:32.169Z","description":"Welcome back! ðŸ”¥ I haven't written anything in a long time, as I've been very busy for the past six months. However, after this time I am back and hopefully permanently. My programming skills have developed a lot since the last time I wrote on my blog. I owe this to my curiosity for technology and advanced programming tools. In this article, I will provide you with an updated list of applications that I use on a daily basis in my work.","tags":["Computer Setup","Programming Tools"],"title":"Software Development & Programming Tools in 2022","socialImage":null}},"allMarkdownRemark":{"edges":[{"node":{"timeToRead":3,"fields":{"tagSlugs":["/blog/tag/computer-setup/","/blog/tag/programming-tools/"],"categorySlug":"/blog/category/software-development/"},"frontmatter":{"title":"My Software Development Setup & Programming Tools (OctoberÂ 2021)","slug":"/blog/my-software-development-setup-and-programming-tools-october-2021","date":"2021-10-15T22:40:32.169Z","category":"Software Development","description":"Many people ask me what tools I use for my work as software full-stack engineer. I will provide a list of the programming languages and frameworks I use, so you know what this list is going to be for. So my tech stack is: JavaScript, TypeScript, PHP, MySQL, PostgreSQL, React, React Native, Node.js, Nest.js, Shopware. In this article, I will present a list of all the tools that I use on a daily basis in my work for software development. ðŸ› ","tags":["Computer Setup","Programming Tools"],"socialImage":{"publicURL":"/static/00555ab136fdacd549b939b0b29dc0ff/thumbnail.jpeg"}}}}]}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/posts/2022-09-14---Software-Development-and-Programming-Tools-In-2022//blog/software-development-and-programming-tools-in-2022","groups":["Computer Setup","Programming Tools"],"id":"322eff88-01b5-5ff2-b8a1-1ae798ad7565"}},"staticQueryHashes":["251939775","2764776372","401334301","63107425"]}